In the case when the deficit angle is more than $\pi$, or equivalently when $A< 1/2$, we can get the geodesic result from a general images prescription \cite{AAT} in case of spacelike separated points:
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{\pi}{2\nu^2 A} G(t, \vartheta) =\left(\frac{1}{2(\cos t -\cos \vartheta)}\right)^{\nu+1} && + \sum_{k=1}^{k_{max}} \left(\frac{1}{2(\cos t -\cos (\vartheta+2\pi A k))}\right)^{\nu+1} + {\nonumber}\\&&
+\sum_{j=1}^{j_{max}} \left(\frac{1}{2(\cos t -\cos (\vartheta-2\pi A j))}\right)^{\nu+1}\!\!\!, \label{geodesicsImages}
\end{eqnarray}
where (square brackets represent the integer part):
